This game requires Unity’s 6000.0.24f1 editor version as well as any computer. It also requires the script to be put in each Dialogue Line 
attached to specific characters as well as the Game Manager. Though intended to be played with headphones, I got to see people have lots of 
fun playing side by side and listening to the music out loud together.

The script is as follows (of course, this is a lot to put in yourself, but video gameplay will be provided as well to watch):

Alejandro:
Ah, another one. Sit down, sit down!
I am Alejandro. It's nice to see a new face.
I have been waiting for six months now…
...all for my first audition.
They keep asking me for more documents.
It never seems like it's enough.
It's good to be thorough...
...I guess.
You might be here a while.
Don't be surprised if you end up waiting years for a chance-

Jing:
Do not let Alejandro scare you.
My name is Jing. It's my 4th time auditioning.
The conductor is not so bad.
He just wants to see that you really want this.
That you are deserving. He's a tough one, for sure.
Huh?
You're being called in?
So soon after your arrival?
Oh my...
Well, good luck then.

Conductor:
....Next.
You will play what is written.
Nothing more....
nothing less.
Begin.

–Mini Game attempt–

Conductor:
Insufficient.
Not what I was looking for at all, actually.
You have completely missed the standard required for my orchestra.
You may try again when I have time.

–Back in Waiting Room–
Alejandro:
Wow.
I've heard similar from others.
The rules change every time you come back.
That is the catch.
But you keep showing up. That is what matters.
Wait-
Again?
Boy, aren't you lucky.
To be called back in so soon!
You've surely made our 5 months together feel like 5 seconds.

Conductor:
You again.
How long has it been?
Hmph...
Let's hope you're ready this time.
My standards have only increased since last time.
Begin.

–Mini Game attempt–

Conductor:
Closer.
But not close enough.
The orchestra requires certainty...
...that you will always play your best.
And your best,
Well,
It wasn't good enough.
Come back when you really mean business.

–Back in Waiting Room–

Jing:
Fourth audition? My, we are long past.
I am on my 9th attempt.
How long has it been since we've last chat?
I wonder...
Regardless,
These auditions...
They're never about the music, are they?
Because even when you pass,
You'll be stuck proving yourself for eternity.
Oh.
It looks like you're up again.
Good Luck.

Conductor:
I'm surprised to see you.
You've really returned?
Most do not make it this far.
They give up after a couple months.
Maybe even years.
Begin.

–Mini Game attempt–

WINNING SEQUENCE:

Conductor:
...
Well...
That was...
Good.
Welcome to the Orchestra....
MY Orchestra.
Remember, I can always remove you...
If you fail to meet my standards.

Narrator:
The Conductor has stamped your papers.
You are official now.
Just remember,
Alejandro and Jing...
are still waiting.
They play just as well as you do.
But luck hasn't given them the chance to prove it.
And there are so many like them.
There are as many as 15 million undocumented immigrants in the US.
Wishing to live the American dream.
Some have been waiting over 10 years.
Just for a chance.
Remember...
to extend kindness to others.
Thanks for playing!


LOSE SEQUENCE:

Conductor:
The Orchestra has made its decision.
Maybe next...year?
Too bad.
Go back to the waiting room.
Until next time.

Narrator:
The door closes.
You can audition next season...or maybe the one after.
Alejandro slides over to make room for you.
Jing is nowhere to be found.
You hear they made the orchestra some time ago.
Alejandro waits for his first audition...
as you wait for yours.
And there are so many like you.
There are as many as 15 million undocumented immigrants in the US.
Wishing to live the American dream.
Some have been waiting over 10 years.
And will continue to wait.
Just for a chance.
Remember...
to extend kindness to others.
Thanks for playing!
